  "slug": "family-chocolate-chip-cookies",
  "title": "Family chocolate chip cookies",
  "subtitle": "A simple cookie recipe scaled for a small batch.",
  "excerpt": "Family chocolate chip cookies. Brown sugar for chew, a pinch of salt to balance, dark chocolate chunks.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "From Rebecca's personal cookbook. A simple chocolate-chip biscuit; recipes of this shape sit in the family-rotation register in most British kitchens.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A short ingredient list and a small batch: eighteen cookies from one bowl, gone the same afternoon."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The brown sugar carries most of the flavour and the chew. A pinch of salt holds the sweetness together. Chill the dough before baking and the cookies hold their shape rather than spreading flat.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What you need",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "name": "Unsalted butter",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 250,
              "prepNote": "softened",
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f3gf000wrkv4p017cubd",
              "ingredientSlug": "unsalted-butter"
            },
            {
              "name": "Light brown sugar",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 200,
              "prepNote": "packed",
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49favj00dxrkv4xnackfrz",
              "ingredientSlug": "light-brown-sugar"
            },
            {
              "name": "Caster sugar",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 100,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49fau900dvrkv4ce3mot41",
              "ingredientSlug": "caster-sugar"
            },
            {
              "name": "Eggs",
              "unit": "each",
              "amount": 2,
              "prepNote": "large",
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f3wj001prkv40f7svjvg",
              "ingredientSlug": "eggs"
            },
            {
              "name": "Vanilla extract",
              "unit": "tsp",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f97x00b3rkv4kdhng3ak",
              "ingredientSlug": "vanilla-extract"
            },
            {
              "name": "Plain flour",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 300,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f2xb0000rkv47vd545ba",
              "ingredientSlug": "plain-flour"
            },
            {
              "name": "Baking powder",
              "unit": "tsp",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f91k00asrkv4txgq60ov",
              "ingredientSlug": "baking-powder"
            },
            {
              "name": "Fine sea salt",
              "unit": "tsp",
              "amount": 0.5,
              "prepNote": null,
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f7kz0086rkv4lsr8ds3o",
              "ingredientSlug": "sea-salt-fine"
            },
            {
              "name": "Dark chocolate",
              "unit": "g",
              "amount": 200,
              "prepNote": "chopped into chunks",
              "groupLabel": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49f95p00azrkv4jkkugcca",
              "ingredientSlug": "dark-chocolate"
            }
          ],
          "defaultServings": 4
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cream the butter and sugars together until pale, three minutes by stand mixer, longer by hand.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add the eggs one at a time, then the vanilla. The mixture should look glossy and smooth.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Sift in the flour, baking powder, and salt. Fold to combine, stop as soon as the flour disappears.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Fold in the chocolate chunks.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cover the bowl and chill for at least thirty minutes. Cold dough spreads less and bakes thicker.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C (fan). Line two baking trays with baking paper.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Drop heaped spoonfuls of dough onto the trays, leave four centimetres between each.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until golden at the edges and just-set in the middle.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cool on the tray for five minutes, then transfer to a wire rack.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Chill the dough for 30 minutes before baking. Preheat the oven properly, 180°C means 180°C on an oven thermometer, not the dial.",
              "cause": "Butter too soft, or oven not hot enough.",
              "symptom": "Cookies spread too thin and crisp"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Stop mixing as soon as the flour disappears. For chewier cookies, replace some plain flour with bread flour for more gluten.",
              "cause": "Over-mixed once the flour went in, or too much flour.",
              "symptom": "Cookies came out cakey, not chewy"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Leave them on the tray for five minutes after baking. They're too soft to move when hot. Lift onto a rack with a palette knife.",
              "cause": "Tried to lift before they'd set.",
              "symptom": "Cookies stuck to the tray"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Use a heavier baking tray, line with baking paper, and bake on the middle shelf.",
              "cause": "Tray too thin, or rack too low.",
              "symptom": "Burnt bottoms, raw middles"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add-ins: 75 g dark chocolate chips, chopped walnuts, dried cranberries, or a pinch of sea salt on top before baking.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Gluten-free: replace plain flour with a 1-to-1 gluten-free blend that includes xanthan gum.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best on the day they are baked, when the edges are crisp and the centres still soft. Store in an airtight tin for up to three days. The dough freezes well in balls; bake from frozen, adding two or three minutes to the time."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "From Rebecca's kitchen. A small batch of eighteen cookies: big enough to share, small enough to finish."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
